Diamondbacks 3, Rockies 0
</SUBHEAD>
<P>
   PHOENIX (AP) -- Off to one of the best starts of his career, Randy Johnson
threw his second shutout and third complete game in four starts as the Arizona
Diamondbacks beat the Colorado Rockies 3-0 on Thursday night. Johnson (4-0)
allowed four hits, struck out eight, walked three and even drove in a run with a
single in the sixth inning.
</P>
