because of possible salmonella contamination. The voluntary recall was taken as
a precaution after some people came down with salmonella in Southern California,
Nevada and Colorado after drinking the products, company spokeswoman Judy Lynes
said Thursday. Fourteen cases have been reported, said Ruth Welch of the U.S.
Food and Drug Administration. Symptoms of salmonella include fever, severe
headache, vomiting, abdominal pain and diarrhea.
