	   KUALA LUMPUR, Malaysia (AP) -- The High Court ruled Friday that Malaysia's
prime minister is not required to testify in the sex trial of an ousted deputy
premier, deflating defense hopes of proving the charges are politically
motivated. Anwar jumped up, shook his fist at the judge and then pounded it on
the wooden guard rail. "Where is justice in this court?" he shouted. "You should
not allow him to hide behind his executive privilege." The judge's decision
ended six months of legal wrangling over a defense subpoena for the prime
minister to answer questions regarding an alleged political conspiracy to frame
Anwar.
</P>
<SUBHEAD>
Columbine Massacre Remembered
</SUBHEAD>
<P>
	   LITTLETON, Colo. (AP) -- In memory of the school shooting massacre,
Coloradans fell silent while a church bell tolled 13 times at 11:21 a.m.
Thursday, the precise moment two teen-agers opened fire in Columbine High School
on April 20, 1999. At private ceremonies and public remembrances all day and
into the night today, students, staff, survivors and strangers came together to
mark the first anniversary of the nation's deadliest school shooting. Gov. Bill
Owens presided over the moment of silence at the state Capitol in Denver that
marked the moment Dylan Klebold and Eric Harris began the bloodbath, killing 12
students and a teacher and wounding 26 before taking their own lives.
</P>
<SUBHEAD>
Document: S.Korea Executed 2,000
</SUBHEAD>
<P>
	   DOKCHON, South Korea (AP) -- According to declassified U.S. military
documents and witnesses, South Korean soldiers and police, observed at times by
U.S. Army officers, executed more than 2,000 political prisoners without trial
in the early weeks of the Korean War. Supreme commander Gen. Douglas MacArthur
became aware of at least one of the mass shootings, according to documents
originally classified "top secret." The new information, detailed in reporting
by The Associated Press and a Korean researcher, substantiates what some
historians have long believed: Large numbers of South Korean leftists arrested
by the right-wing regime were secretly killed.
</P>
