	   NEW YORK (AP) -- Melvin Mora hit his first major league home run, connecting
in the 10th inning Thursday night to give the New York Mets a 5-4 win over the
Milwaukee Brewers for a three-game sweep. Mora's drive over the center-field
fence against Curtis Leskanic (0-1) came in his 88th at-bat in the majors. The
Mets won their fourth in a row, and beat the Brewers for the eighth straight
time.
</P>
