<DATE_TIME> 2000-04-21 07:24 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Giuliani Wife Joining 'Vagina' Play  </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
   NEW YORK (AP) -- Actress and television personality Donna
Hanover, the wife of Mayor Rudolph Giuliani, is joining the cast of
the off-Broadway hit ''The Vagina Monologues'' next month.
</P>
<P>
   Beginning May 30, Hanover will take over a lead role in the play
written by Eve Ensler, a personal friend and political supporter of
Hillary Rodham Clinton, Giuliani's opponent in the U.S. Senate
race.
</P>
<P>
   Joannie Danielides, Hanover's spokeswoman, confirmed the
casting. Calls seeking comment from the mayor's office were not
immediately returned early today.
</P>
<P>
   Hanover will perform in the stage show for two weeks, sharing
the play's dozen or so monologues with two other women.
</P>
<P>
   The monologues are constructed from interviews Ensler held with
women on topics including orgasm, uncomfortable pelvic exams,
sexual abuse, sexual fantasies and childbirth.
</P>
<P>
   Ensler had been performing all of the monologues herself until
February, when the she began sharing the lead with rotating trios
of performers, including Broadway performers such as Audra McDonald
and singer Alanis Morissette.
</P>
<P>
   Hanover has appeared on the big screen in films including ''The
People vs. Larry Flynt'' and ''Light it Up,'' and on TV in soap
operas such as ''One Life to Live'' and ''All My Children.'' She
also is the host of a program on the Food Network.
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
