<HEADLINE> Train Deaths Suspect Held  </HEADLINE>
By CHRISTOPHER NEWTON, Associated Press Writer
<TEXT>
<P>
   SINKING SPRING, Pa. (AP) -- A man was arrested today and charged
with four counts of homicide for allegedly pushing the car of his
former girlfriend into the path of an oncoming train, killing her
and three others.
</P>
<P>
   Candace Wertz made a frantic 911 call on her cellular phone and
was talking to a dispatcher when her car was struck by the train
Thursday, state police Cpl. Bruce Edwards said.
</P>
<P>
   Carlos Angel Diaz Santiago, 22, of West Reading was taken into
custody this morning and charged with homicide and aggravated
assault, said state police Lt. Edward Snyder. Details of the arrest
were not immediately available.
</P>
<P>
   Also taken into custody but not arrested was an unidentified man
who was believed to be in the car Thursday when Santiago allegedly
rear-ended Wertz's car and then pushed it in front of the train,
Snyder said.
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
