<HEADLINE> Teacher Suspended for Spit Incident  </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
   SUGAR LAND, Texas (AP) -- School officials are investigating
allegations a second-grade teacher ordered students to punish a
pupil by spitting on him.
</P>
<P>
   Madeline Raven, 27, was placed on leave Thursday, said school
district spokeswoman Martha Morrow.
</P>
<P>
   Yolanda Clark said she learned of the incident when she picked
up her 8-year-old son David from Briargate Elementary on Wednesday.
He had on a different shirt from the one he wore to school.
</P>
<P>
   ''When I asked him where his other shirt was, he said the
teacher had made the other children spit all over him,'' she said.
''I just couldn't believe it when he told me. He said he didn't
want to go to school anymore.''
</P>
<P>
   Clark said David and another student were involved in a spitting
contest when the teacher caught them. For punishment, the teacher
ordered other students to spit on David, the boy's mother said.
</P>
<P>
   Sugar Land is a suburb of Houston.
</P>
</TEXT>
