<HEADLINE> Spending Plans for Tobacco Money  </HEADLINE>
By The Associated Press	   How states plan to spend their shares of tobacco
settlements. In
1998, 46 states agreed to a $206 billion settlement, to be paid out
over 25 years. Florida, Minnesota, Mississippi and Texas had
already reached their own deals for a combined $40 billion.
