<P>
   Vietnam Economy Stuck at Crossroads
</P>
<P>
   HANOI, Vietnam (AP) -- International investors flooded in when
the United States lifted the embargo against its former wartime
enemy in 1994. Yet the tantalizing potential of a largely untouched
market of 76 million people, cheap resources and a young,
well-educated labor pool has yet to be realized. Vietnam remains a
work in progress. Blossoming potential is being threatened by a
faltering economy, slowed reforms and a frustrating business
climate that has left foreign investors wary.
</P>
<P>
