</P>
<P>
   EAGAN, Minn. (AP) -- Northwest Airlines flight attendants will
decide whether to ratify a tentative five-year contract to end a
bitter 3{-year battle with the nation's fourth-largest carrier.
Ballots will be mailed next week to the airline's 11,000 flight
attendants, who rejected a tentative agreement last August. They
have been seeking a new contract since September 1996. Northwest
pilots went on a 15-day strike in 1998 that crippled the airline
for weeks and cost the company millions.
