<HEADLINE> Body pulled from river identified as missing Collingswood woman  </HEADLINE>
By JOHN CURRAN, Associated Press Writer
<TEXT>
<P>
   COLLINGSWOOD, N.J. (AP) -- A body found floating in the Cooper
River was identified Friday as that of a woman abducted from her
apartment in December.
</P>
<P>
   It took a forensic dentist to identify the remains of Chia Yen
''Ann'' Hsu, 30, of Collingswood, whose nude, bound body remained
submerged in the Cooper River for more than four months.
</P>
<P>
   The condition of the body made it impossible for Camden County
Medical Examiner Robert J. Segal and Haskell Askin, the forensic
dentist who identified her, to establish a cause of death beyond
saying Hsu was murdered.
</P>
<P>
   Hsu's body was spotted floating in the Camden river by two
passers-by Thursday. She had been missing since disappearing from
her first-floor apartment in what authorities say was a brutal,
random attack.
</P>
<P>
   Her hands and feet were bound with electrical cords and a
telephone cord taken from her apartment, according to First
Assistant Camden County Prosecutor James P. Lynch. An autopsy
performed Friday showed multiple skull fractures around the
forehead, he said.
</P>
<P>
   Lynch said the skull fractures were inflicted before the body
was submerged, but it wasn't clear whether she died before she
entered the river.
</P>
<P>
   Prosecutors have already charged Rodney Bullock, 20, with
robbing, raping and dumping Hsu in the river. She was last seen
alive Dec. 7.
</P>
<P>
   ''There are no words to describe how painful and horrifying this
experience has been,'' said Hsu family friend Andy McLaughlin, who
read a statement prepared by the woman's family. ''Ann will always
be with us in our minds and hearts.''
</P>
<P>
   Hsu was reported missing after she failed to show up at her job.
Police found her apartment ransacked, the telephone line cut and
evidence of forced entry and robbery. Her black 1998 Honda Civic
was also missing.
</P>
<P>
   Bullock, of Camden, was captured in North Carolina, where he was
seen driving Hsu's car. He reportedly confessed to authorities, but
Lynch would not confirm that Friday.
</P>
<P>
   A transient high-school dropout with a criminal record that
included drug and burglary charges, he is charged with murder,
kidnapping, aggravated sexual assault and burglary.
</P>
<P>
   He is 5-foot-8 inches tall and weighs 210 pounds.
</P>
<P>
   Hsu, a Drexel University graduate who worked as a consultant in
Bala Cynwyd, Pa., and was engaged to be married, was 5-3, 108
pounds.
</P>
<P>
   ''We hope you'll share in our memory of Ann by appreciating each
other more as well,'' McLaughlin said, reading from the family's
statement at a news conference.
</P>
<P>
   Bullock's case is awaiting presentment to a grand jury. No
decision has been made on whether to seek the death penalty, Lynch
said.
</P>
<P>
   On Feb. 27, the family held an emotional two-hour memorial
ceremony for Hsu. No new service is planned, according to
McLaughlin.
</P>
<P>
   The discovery of the body closed the book on what was a painful
chapter for investigators and volunteers who helped search for Hsu
in the weeks after her disappearance, Lynch said.
</P>
<P>
   ''This is one of these cases you take with you,'' Police Chief
Thomas Garrity told The Courier-Post of Cherry Hill in Friday's
editions. ''This is a day we have been waiting for to hopefully
bring some closure.''
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
<TRAILER> AP-ES-04-21-00 1808 </TRAILER>
