<HEADLINE> 6 Indicted in 3-Ton Cocaine Seizure  </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
   TAMPA, Fla. (AP) -- Six crew members on a ship have been indicted
on drug charges after the seizure of three tons of cocaine off the
coast of Ecuador.
</P>
<P>
   The ship Layneyd was intercepted April 5 by the Navy ship USS
John A Moore. A Coast Guard detachment found the ship to be
carrying more than 3 tons of cocaine.
</P>
<P>
   The drug shipment was determined to be related to an ongoing
investigation by federal authorities in Tampa, U.S. Attorney Donna
Bucella said in a statement Friday.
</P>
