<HEADLINE> Braves 6, Pirates 2  </HEADLINE>
By TOM SALADINO, AP Sports Writer
<TEXT>
<P>
   ATLANTA (AP) -- Terry Mulholland pitched Atlanta's first complete
game of the season, and Andres Galarraga hit a go-ahead single in a
two-run sixth inning to lead the Atlanta Braves to their fifth
straight win, 6-2 over the Pittsburgh Pirates on Friday night.
</P>
<P>
   Mulholland (2-2) allowed eight hits, two walks and struck out
three in his first complete game since June 18, 1997. Mulholland
has 46 career complete games.
</P>
<P>
   Galarraga, who hit a pair of home runs and drove in four runs in
Thursday night's 6-4 win over Philadelphia, singled to left to
score Chipper Jones to snap a 2-2 tie in the sixth off reliever
Mike Garcia (0-1).
</P>
<P>
   Jones opened the sixth with a walk and took second on a single
by Brian Jordan. Jordan took third on Galarraga's hit and scored on
a sacrifice fly by Javy Lopez.
</P>
<P>
   The Braves added two more runs in the seventh on RBI singles by
Quilvio Veras and Andruw Jones. Veras went 3-for-3 with a walk, and
two RBIs.
</P>
<P>
   The Pirates had tied it at 2 in the sixth on a solo home run by
Aramis Ramirez, who had been in a 1-for-22 slump before hitting an
0-1 pitch from Mulholland into the left-field stands.
</P>
<P>
   The Braves had gone ahead 2-1 in the fifth on an RBI single by
Veras off Pittsburgh starter Jose Parra. Atlanta's first run came
on a run-scoring single by Chipper Jones in the first.
</P>
<P>
   Parra allowed two runs and five hits in five innings with seven
strikeouts.
</P>
<P>
   Pittsburgh's first run came in the second on an RBI single by
Jason Kendall, who has hit in eight straight games.
</P>
<P>
Notes: Pittsburgh has lost four of five games. ... LHP Steve
Avery, coming back from offseason shoulder surgery, makes his third
rehab start Saturday. He'll pitch for the Braves' Greenville
Double-A club against Mobile. ... Parra, 27, was recalled Thursday
from Triple-A Nashville. His last appearance in the majors was
Sept. 29, 1996 with Minnesota. He pitched in Korea in 1998 and in
Japan last season. ... The Pirates have lost six straight games at
Turner Field and are 1-9 in their last 10 games in Atlanta).
</P>
</TEXT>
