<HEADLINE> Guatemala 2, Panama 1  </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
   HERSHEY, Pa. (AP) -- Carlos Ruiz scored twice to lead Guatemala
over Panama 2-1 Friday in the opening game of the final round of
Olympic soccer qualifying from North and Central America and the
Caribbean.
</P>
<P>
   Ruiz scored in the 27th minute off a centering pass from Freddy
Garcia, but Antonio Ortega tied it with a 7-yard header off Manuel
Torres' free kick in the 29th.
</P>
<P>
   Ruiz scored the game-winner in the 80th, going up the middle of
the field and beating goalkeeper Oscar MacFarlane.
</P>
<P>
   Both teams play Mexico in their final first-round game, with
Guatemala playing Sunday and Panama Tuesday.
</P>
<P>
   The United States, in the other group with Canada and Honduras,
opened with a 3-0 win over the Hondurans later Friday.
</P>
<P>
   The top two teams in each group advance, and the two semifinal
winners qualify for the Sydney Games.
</P>
<P>
   Olympic men's soccer is limited to players under 23 years old,
except each team can use three wild-card players over the age
limit.
</P>
</TEXT>
